definition:
ὕμνος, -ου, ὁ 
 [in LXX for תְּהִלָּה, נְגִינָה, שִׁיר, etc. ;] 
a hymn; 
  (a) in cl. a festal song in praise of gods or heroes; 
   (b) in LXX and NT a song of praise addressed to God: Eph.5:19, Col.3:16.†
  SYN.: ψαλμός, that which is sung to a musical accompaniment; ᾠδή, the generic term for song (cf. Tr., Syn., § LXXviii, Lft. on Col.3:16)  (AS)
